sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant MRREST as Model Registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over Client, PG: Flow 1: Model Registry REST API Access via Route (OpenShift)
    Client->>Router: POST /v2/model_registry/<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (JWT)<br/>HTTPS TLS
    Router->>KRBAC: Forward (TLS reencrypt)<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    KRBAC->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>KRBAC: Token Valid + Authorized
    KRBAC->>MRREST: Proxy request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: None (validated by proxy)
    MRREST->>PG: Query/Persist data<br/>5432/TCP PostgreSQL<br/>Auth: Username/Password<br/>Encryption: Configurable TLS
    PG-->>MRREST: Query Results
    MRREST-->>KRBAC: Response
    KRBAC-->>Router: Response (TLS)
    Router-->>Client: JSON Response (HTTPS)

    participant Operator as Model Registry Operator
    participant OSConfig as config.openshift.io<br/>Ingress API
    participant AuthCR as Platform Auth CR<br/>services.platform.opendatahub.io

    Note over Operator, AuthCR: Flow 2: Operator Reconciliation
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: ModelRegistry CR event
    Operator->>OSConfig: Read cluster ingress domain<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    OSConfig-->>Operator: Ingress domain config
    Operator->>AuthCR: Read admin groups<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    AuthCR-->>Operator: Admin group list
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update managed resources<br/>(Deployment, Service, Route, NetworkPolicy, RBAC)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources created/updated

    participant MigMgr as StorageMigrationManager
    participant MigAPI as migration.k8s.io API

    Note over MigMgr, MigAPI: Flow 3: Storage Version Migration
    MigMgr->>K8sAPI: Check CRD Status.StoredVersions<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    K8sAPI-->>MigMgr: StoredVersions list
    alt Kubernetes StorageVersionMigration API available
        MigMgr->>MigAPI: Create StorageVersionMigration<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        MigAPI-->>MigMgr: Migration status
    else Fallback: manual re-read/re-write
        MigMgr->>K8sAPI: List all ModelRegistry resources<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        K8sAPI-->>MigMgr: ModelRegistry list
        MigMgr->>K8sAPI: Update each resource (re-write)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        K8sAPI-->>MigMgr: Updated
    end
